Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.01,0:00:07.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们将繁星摘下\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We pulled the stars from the skies...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.92,0:00:14.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}用来装点地球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}...and brought them down to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.35,0:00:27.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}代价是什么呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But at what cost?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.11,0:00:31.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当我们点亮所有的灯同时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When we turned on all these lights...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.28,0:00:33.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也失去了一些宝贵的东西\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we lost something precious.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.78,0:00:36.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}繁星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.82,0:02:30.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\fe134}{\fsp0}{\fad(500,500)}{\pos(190,278)}{\fn方正准圆简体}{\bord0}{\fs20}{\c&H24EFFF&}宇宙大探索\N{\fs17}{\c&HFFFFFF&} 第八集
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.40,0:02:40.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很久以前 只靠火光照亮\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A long time ago, in a world lit only by fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.20,0:02:42.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们和繁星之间的关系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our relationship with the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.03,0:02:44.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}非常的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was far more...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.30,0:02:45.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}贴心\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}personal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.81,0:02:47.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几千代人以来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For thousands of generations,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.51,0:02:50.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们将繁星视作生活不可或缺的部分\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we watched the stars as if our lives depended on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.74,0:02:53.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}确实如此\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because they did.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.67,0:02:57.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们人类不算最大\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We humans were not the biggest, the strongest,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.71,0:03:00.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也不是最强壮或者最快的相比其它动物而言\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&} nor the fastest of all the animals we competed against.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.59,0:03:02.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但我们有个特长\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But we did have one thing going for us...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.59,0:03:04.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的智慧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.36,0:03:08.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其中一点就是识别图形的天赋\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One aspect of that was a genius for pattern recognition
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.19,0:03:10.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}夜复一夜 我们仰望星空\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Night after night, we watched the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.90,0:03:13.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的祖先慢慢地注意到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And over time, our ancestors noticed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.87,0:03:18.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}夜空中星星的移动预示着地球上的变化\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the motions of the stars across the nights of the year foretold changes on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.87,0:03:21.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}威胁或者增加我们生存的机会\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that threatened or enhanced our chances for survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.74,0:03:26.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在我们只能依靠想象力来体会故事的年代\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In a time when our imaginations were the only stage where stories came to life,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.61,0:03:28.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那时没有电影或者电视\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before there were movies or TVs
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.38,0:03:30.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也没有其它的电子设备\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or electronic devices of any kind,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.88,0:03:35.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不同的文明将这些点连成各自不同的图案\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every human culture connected the dots to form their own pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.72,0:03:40.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些图案变成故事书中的插图\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These images became the illustrations of a storybook
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.63,0:03:44.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}更深层面说来 也是一本生存手册\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that, on a deeper level, was also a survival manual.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.46,0:03:47.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}天神和英雄们的名字个性\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The names and personalities of the gods, heroes,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.57,0:03:49.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有动物或者类似物体的名字和个性\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}farm animals or familiar objects
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.74,0:03:51.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在各个文化中各不相同\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}varied from culture to culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.94,0:03:56.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}除了一组特定的美丽星团\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there was one particularly gorgeous group of stars
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.38,0:04:00.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从古希腊人到现在的我们都叫它\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}known to the Ancient Greeks and to us today
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.11,0:04:02.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}昴宿星团\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as the Pleiades,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.11,0:04:05.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}其位于金牛座 裸眼就可以轻易的看见 肉眼通常见到有六颗亮星
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.45,0:04:05.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大约1亿年前形成的星团\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a star cluster formed about 100 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.95,0:04:09.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每颗星都比太阳明亮40倍左右\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each of them is some 40 times brighter than our Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.29,0:04:12.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}昴宿六是最亮的一颗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And Alcyone, the most luminous,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.29,0:04:15.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比太阳亮1000倍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}outshines our Sun 1,000 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.83,0:04:18.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以前昂宿星团被用来检测视力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For ages, the Pleiades have been used as an eye test
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.80,0:04:22.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而且世界通用\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for people all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.13,0:04:24.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}能看到6颗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you could see at least six of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.00,0:04:26.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就是普通人的标准\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you were considered normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.84,0:04:28.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看到超过7颗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you saw more than seven,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.67,0:04:31.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就符合战士或者侦察兵的标准了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you were an ideal candidate for a warrior or scout.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.81,0:04:34.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对于古凯尔特人和不列颠群岛的德鲁伊特来说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Among the Ancient Celts and Druids of the British Isles,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.98,0:04:38.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们相信昂宿星团和亡魂有关\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Pleiades were believed to have a haunting significance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.35,0:04:42.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一年中它们升到天空最高点的那一晚的午夜\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On the night of the year that they reach the highest point in the sky at midnight,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.42,0:04:46.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}亡魂会在地球上游荡\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the spirits of the dead were thought to wander the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.09,0:04:48.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}据信这是一个节日的起源\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is believed to be the origin of the holiday
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.00,0:04:51.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以前叫萨温节\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}once known as Samhain,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.10,0:04:52.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}现在叫万圣节\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}now called Halloween.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.63,0:04:54.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在世界各地 我们的祖先用\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All over the Earth, our ancestors told
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.97,0:04:57.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}各种神奇的故事\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}wonderful stories to explain
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.04,0:05:00.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}来解释昂宿星团的来历\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how the Pleiades came to be in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.44,0:05:02.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以北美洲的基奥瓦人来说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For the Kiowa people of North America,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.81,0:05:04.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}故事是这样的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it happened something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.65,0:05:15.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很久很久以前 一些小姑娘\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Long, long ago, some young women
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.45,0:05:17.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}溜出他们的营地\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}snuck away from their campsite
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.56,0:05:19.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在星空下无拘无束的跳舞\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to dance freely beneath the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.69,0:05:55.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}山神 救命啊\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Rock, save us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.43,0:05:59.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}山神 可怜可怜我们吧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Rock, take pity on us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.03,0:06:03.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}山神听到了她们的哭声 升起了一座高高的山峰\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The rock heard their cries and grew taller.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.91,0:06:13.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}变成了今天的魔鬼峰\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Until it became what is today known as the Devil's Tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.72,0:06:21.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些姑娘变成了昂宿星团的星星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The maidens were transformed into the stars of the Pleiades,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.02,0:06:25.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}冬至的时候可以看到她们高高的挂在山峰上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which may be seen hanging above the tower in midwinter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.53,0:06:29.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}古希腊人也将这7颗明珠\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Ancient Greeks also saw those seven jewels
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.86,0:06:31.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看做7位少女\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as seven maidens,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.96,0:06:35.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}阿特拉斯的7个女儿\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the seven daughters of Atlas,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.96,0:06:35.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}负责以肩顶天的神
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.57,0:06:40.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}指的是猎户座的那个猎户
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.57,0:06:40.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不是被熊追 而是被俄里翁追\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}pursued not by bears, but by...Orion the hunter
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.31,0:06:43.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他出来溜达的时候看到了她们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who spied them when he was out walking one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.29,0:06:55.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}俄里翁这个猎户兽性大发\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Orion became mad with desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.90,0:07:06.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}追了她们7年 直到有一天\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For seven years, he chased them relentlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.23,0:07:10.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}终于精疲力尽了 -宙斯 救命啊\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}- Exhausted... - Zeus, help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.60,0:07:13.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她们向宙斯呼救\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}...they prayed to Zeus for deliverance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.24,0:07:19.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}众神之王宙斯大发慈悲\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Zeus, the king of the gods, felt sorry for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.75,0:07:21.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}把她们7个\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and transformed those seven maidens
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.98,0:07:25.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}变成了昂宿星团\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into the Pleiades.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.79,0:07:36.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是 神就是神经病\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the gods are, if anything, capricious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.16,0:07:39.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}俄里翁被蝎子蛰死后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When Orion was killed by the sting of a scorpion,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.77,0:07:45.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宙斯把他放在上天 让他可以继续追逐这7位姐妹\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Zeus placed him in the sky where he could resume his pursuit of the seven gorgeous sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.10,0:07:48.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的祖先编织了各种美丽的传说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our ancestors, they wove brilliantly imaginative stories
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.84,0:07:52.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是除了想象 并不能让我们更接近这些星星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But they can bring us no closer to the stars than our dreams
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.68,0:07:55.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}直到很多年后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It took yet another few thousand years
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.48,0:08:00.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}才有3位聪明的科学家揭开了这些星星的神秘面纱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}until three brilliant scientists unlocked the secrets of the true lives of the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.74,0:08:15.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1901年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1901,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.41,0:08:18.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哈佛是男人的天下\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Harvard was a man's world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.38,0:08:21.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}直到一位名叫爱德华・查尔斯・皮克林的天文学家\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But an astronomer named Edward Charles Pickering
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.14,0:08:22.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}打破了这个规矩\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}broke that rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.72,0:08:28.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}噢 皮克林的办公室就在走廊尽头\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Oh, Pickering's office is just down the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.69,0:08:30.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那扇门的后面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that door over there leads to the room
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.89,0:08:34.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就是他的机房\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where he keeps his computers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.10,0:08:48.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}说起来 这些女人都是「计算器」 但是\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're supposed to call those women "computers," but, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.84,0:08:51.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我听到不少人叫她们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I've heard more than one fellow refer to those gals
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.44,0:08:54.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}皮克林的后宫\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as "Pickering's Harem."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.38,0:08:56.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}皮克林招募了一群妇女\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pickering assembled a team of women
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.75,0:08:59.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}给星星分类 绘制星图\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to map and classify the types of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.75,0:09:03.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其中一位为我们了解恒星的物质提供了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of them provided the key to our understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.22,0:09:04.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}关键的钥匙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the substance of the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.92,0:09:07.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有一位给我们提供了计算\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And another devised a way for us to calculate
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.76,0:09:10.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙体积的方法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the size of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.73,0:09:14.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你可能从没听说过她们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For some reason, you probably never heard of either of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.40,0:09:16.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想知道原因吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Wonder why.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.54,0:09:22.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个小组的组长名叫安妮・坎农\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's Annie Jump Cannon, the leader of the team.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.24,0:09:24.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}完成时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Before she was through,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.14,0:09:26.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她分类了25万颗恒星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}she catalogued a quarter of a million stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.25,0:09:31.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}11号是一颗B7星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Number 11 is a B7.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.75,0:09:34.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是昂宿星团的昂宿六\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's Alcyone in the Pleiades.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.72,0:09:37.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在坎农还年轻的时候\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cannon lost her hearing during a bout of scarlet fever
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.25,0:09:38.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她不幸因为感染猩红热而丧失了听力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when she was a young woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.49,0:09:41.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}12号是一颗B6星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Number 12 is a B6.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.93,0:09:44.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是亨丽爱塔・勒维特 也是失聪\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's Henrietta Swan Leavitt. She's also deaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.80,0:09:48.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她是这里的另一位伟大的科学家\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And she's the other great scientist in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.77,0:09:53.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}勒维特发明了天文学家沿用上百年的方法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Leavitt discovered the law that astronomers still use more than a century later
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.74,0:09:55.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}用来测量恒星之间的距离\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to measure the distances to the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.61,0:09:58.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有宇宙的体积\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the size of the cosmos itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.14,0:10:03.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}安妮・坎农在一张贺卡中说明了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Annie Jump Cannon sent out a Christmas card explaining
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.08,0:10:06.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她们正在从事的工作\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what she and her sisters were actually doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.15,0:10:08.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恒星发出的光可以\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The light from a star is allowed
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.12,0:10:11.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}通过望远镜中的棱镜 她写道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to fall through a prism placed in the telescope, she wrote.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.62,0:10:15.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}经过放大 星光可以分解成一组色带\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thus magnified, the starlight is split up into a band
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.33,0:10:17.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}显示出组成的颜色\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}showing its component colors,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.76,0:10:22.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}红光和紫光分别处于两端\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the red rays going to one end and the violet to the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.10,0:10:24.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是恒星的光谱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the spectrum of the star.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.47,0:10:27.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由深色细线表示\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It shows the presence of fine, dark lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.37,0:10:31.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将这些细线与实验室中发光物质做对比\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By comparing them with lines given by glowing substances in the laboratory
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.84,0:10:35.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们可以断定这些地球上熟悉的物质\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we can determine that the same elements familiar to us
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.48,0:10:38.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}同样存在于遥远的恒星上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the Earth also exist in the outermost star.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.79,0:10:53.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是12358B号\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is plate number 12358B.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.84,0:11:03.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这块板上的第一号是颗B类星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Number one at this plate is a B-type star.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.58,0:11:09.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}定为B2\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Make that a B2.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.35,0:11:13.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}坎农用了几十年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It took Cannon decades
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.08,0:11:14.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}按照光谱特性\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to classify the spectral character
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.99,0:11:17.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为成千上万的恒星分门别类\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of hundreds of thousands of stars
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.42,0:11:19.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}根据她制定的方法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}according to the scheme that she devised.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.99,0:11:22.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}坎农认为恒星可以\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cannon discovered that the stars fell
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.43,0:11:28.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}根据它们的光谱线图被分为7大类\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into a continuous sequence of seven broad categories according to their spectral line patterns.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.87,0:11:31.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每个大类由一个字母代表\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each was designated by a letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.24,0:11:35.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是相同类别的两颗恒星的光谱线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the spectral lines of two stars in the same letter class
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.17,0:11:37.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可能有着细微的区别\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could differ in subtle ways,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.34,0:11:41.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}坎农根据记忆察觉到的细微变化\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}minute variations that Cannon learned to recognize from memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.25,0:11:43.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为了区分这些光谱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To distinguish these spectra from one another,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.91,0:11:48.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她又将每大类分为10个用数字代表的小类\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}she assigned ten numerical subcategories for each class.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.59,0:11:51.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}安妮・坎农将恒星归类\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Annie Jump Cannon organized the stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.42,0:11:56.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}另一位科学家负责解密她的成果中隐藏的含义\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it would fall to another scientist to decipher the hidden meaning in her work
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.06,0:12:01.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1923年的英格兰 妇女无权\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the England of 1923, women were forbidden
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.53,0:12:03.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在科学上获得高级学位\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from pursuing advanced degrees in science.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.90,0:12:06.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是塞西莉亚・佩恩在伦敦参加了一个讲座\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Cecelia Payne had attended a lecture in London
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.80,0:12:09.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由阿瑟・爱丁顿爵士演讲\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the astronomer Sir Arthur Eddington,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.07,0:12:11.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他是首位证实\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the first scientist to provide evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.71,0:12:15.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}爱因斯坦广义相对论的科学家\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that Einstein's revolutionary General Theory of Relativity was correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.58,0:12:17.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从那时起\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From that moment on,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.11,0:12:18.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她知道没什么可以阻挡她\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}she knew that nothing would deter her
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.82,0:12:21.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}追求她的梦想\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from pursing her big dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.79,0:12:25.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她决定移居美国\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}She resolved to emigrate to America,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.16,0:12:29.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在那里妇女已经有了研究恒星的自由\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where women had already gained the freedom to study the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.63,0:12:32.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哈佛大学接受了她的申请\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Her application was accepted at Harvard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.66,0:12:37.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她随后的发现改变了一个天文学的基本观点\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What she would discover there would challenge one of the central beliefs of astronomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.30,0:12:43.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}造成的影响就如同现代天文物理学的曙光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The resulting impact would be the dawn of modern astrophysics.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.64,0:12:54.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几十年过去了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the decades passed,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.48,0:12:57.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}安妮・坎农和她的组员不断地筛分恒星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Annie Jump Cannon and her team kept sifting the stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.71,0:12:59.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}检查每一颗的光谱特征\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}checking each one's spectral signature
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.55,0:13:02.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并将它们归入\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with a fleeting glance and then dropping them
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.39,0:13:04.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}7大分类中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into one of seven categories.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.22,0:13:07.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们变成了图片中成千上万的像素\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They became hundreds of thousands of dots
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.06,0:13:10.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在当时还没人能够了解它的含义\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a larger picture which no one could yet understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.39,0:13:15.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这支队伍中又来了一位新的成员\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Into this community of women came one more.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.67,0:13:18.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哈喽\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, hello there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.40,0:13:21.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你就是佩恩吧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You must be Miss Payne.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.57,0:13:22.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}等你好久啦\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We've been waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.87,0:13:25.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}快进来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Come on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.08,0:13:30.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}塞西莉亚・佩恩第一次在科研环境中受到这样的欢迎\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cecilia Payne had never experienced such kindness in a scientific setting before.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.35,0:13:35.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}姐妹们无私的与她分享研究成果\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This sisterhood generously shared the fruits of their labors with her,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.12,0:13:36.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她将她们的观察结果\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and she turned their observations
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.95,0:13:40.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}转化成一种对恒星的全新认识\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into a radical new understanding of the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.52,0:13:43.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}两个女人变成了非常要好的朋友\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The two women became great friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.66,0:13:46.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}坎农把恒星光谱对佩恩倾囊相授\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cannon taught Payne everything she had learned about stellar spectra
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.93,0:13:48.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}佩恩着手分析坎农的资料\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And Payne began to analyze Cannon's data
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.73,0:13:54.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}尝试着判断恒星中的化学成分与物理状态\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to see if she could determine the actual chemical composition and physical state of the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.71,0:13:58.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她发挥了她的理论原子物理学专长\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}She brought to this work her expertise in theoretical and atomic physics
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.71,0:14:04.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恒星光谱中最突出的特征\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The most prominent features in the spectra of stars
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.58,0:14:10.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}显示了重金属元素的存在 比如钙 和铁\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}showed the presence of heavy elements such as calcium... and iron,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.29,0:14:13.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球上最常见的那些元素\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which are among the most abundant elements in the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.26,0:14:15.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}天文学家自然而然的得出结论\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So astronomers naturally concluded
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.26,0:14:19.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恒星是由与地球相同的物质组成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the stars were made of the same elements as the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.10,0:14:21.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就连比例都大致相同\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and in roughly the same proportions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.26,0:14:26.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1924年 当时的美国天文学泰斗亨利・诺利斯・罗素\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1924, Henry Norris Russell was the dean
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.17,0:14:31.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为我们对于恒星的了解做出了重大的贡献\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of American astronomers having made major contributions to our understanding of the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.84,0:14:36.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球上的40到45号化学元素\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}40 to 45 of the chemical elements that we have here on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.48,0:14:39.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一样存在与太阳的光谱中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are also present in the spectrum of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.28,0:14:42.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所以我们可以推断太阳的成分\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we can assume that the composition of the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.82,0:14:45.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与地球类似\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}resembles that of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.69,0:14:49.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果有人能把地壳加热到发出光芒\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If one were to heat the crust of the Earth to incandescence,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.19,0:14:52.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的光谱就会和太阳类似\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its spectrum would resemble that of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.34,0:15:13.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}安妮 我明白了这么多年来你的工作成果的真正意义\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Annie, I think I now understand what it all means. All your years of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.22,0:15:14.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}说来听听\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.48,0:15:18.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我计算了不同温度下的光谱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I've calculated what the spectra should look like across a wide range of temperatures,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.19,0:15:22.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们和你的分类法完美吻合\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they match your system of classification perfectly
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.69,0:15:26.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恒星的光谱可以表示它的温度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The spectrum of any star tells you exactly how hot it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.90,0:15:32.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你的OBAFGKM就是恒星的温标\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Your "O-B-A-F-G-K-M" is really a temperature scale of the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.90,0:15:32.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}OBAFGKM=哈佛分类法 各个字母代表不同的光谱类别
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.90,0:15:35.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从最热到最冷\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the hottest to the coldest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.57,0:15:40.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}重点来了 安妮 多亏了你\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here's the headline, Annie. Thanks to your work,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.41,0:15:44.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我发现 恒星几乎全部是由氢和氦组成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I've discovered that the stars are made almost entirely of hydrogen and helium.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.15,0:15:49.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恒星中的氢和氦比金属多上百万倍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's a million times more hydrogen and helium than the metals in the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.42,0:15:52.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我知道听上去好像挺傻\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I know, it sounds daft.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.09,0:15:54.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你确定吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Are you certain?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.16,0:15:58.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有人核对过你的计算结果吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Has anyone else checked your calculations?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.90,0:16:01.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还没 我都写进我的论文里了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Not yet, but it's all in my thesis,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.50,0:16:03.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}已经寄给罗素教授了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is already on its way to Professor Russell.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.55,0:16:17.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}倒霉孩子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Poor woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.61,0:16:20.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}罗素对她表示遗憾\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Russell felt sorry for Cecilia Payne.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.88,0:16:24.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在他看来 她的论文从根本上就是错的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Her thesis appeared to him to be fundamentally flawed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.96,0:16:38.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}显然氢和氦不可能比金属多上百万倍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is clearly impossible that hydrogen should be a million times more abundant than the metals.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.31,0:16:48.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她仔细收集的证据与传统的科学观点不相符\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Her carefully gathered evidence flew in the face of conventional scientific wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.78,0:16:50.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我怎么可能是对的 她问\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"How could I be right," she asked,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.75,0:16:52.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那就意味着\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"if that must mean
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.98,0:16:55.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那么著名的科学家错了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that such a distinguished scientist was wrong?"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.65,0:17:00.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}尽管她对自己的研究结果很自信\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Despite her confidence in the quality of her research,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.72,0:17:03.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她还是在她的论文里加上了一句 「高的几乎可以肯定不真实」\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}she caved and added a sentence to her thesis
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.83,0:17:06.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}动摇了这个非常伟大的观点\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that undermined its greatest insight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.34,0:17:13.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}4年后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would be four years
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.80,0:17:16.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}罗素才意识到佩恩是正确的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before Russell realized that Payne was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.57,0:17:19.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}值得表扬的是 他一认识到这点\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To his credit, as soon as he did,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.74,0:17:22.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他就承认了 这是佩恩的发现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he acknowledged that it was her discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.52,0:17:29.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}佩恩的《恒星大气》被普遍看做是\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Payne's "Stellar Atmospheres" is widely regarded
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.35,0:17:33.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}天文学有史以来最杰出的博士论文\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as the most brilliant PhD thesis ever written in astronomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.32,0:17:37.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它成了这个领域里教科书\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It became the standard text in its field.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.69,0:17:41.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有坚持我的观点是我的责任\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I was to blame for not having pressed my point.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.43,0:17:46.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}尽管我相信自己的正确 却还是屈服于权威\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I had given in to authority when I believed I was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.30,0:17:48.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果你对自己的结论有把握\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you are sure of your facts,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.37,0:17:50.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你就应该坚持你的立场\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you should defend your position.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.37,0:17:50.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}恒星大气学
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.21,0:17:56.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在其它领域 权威的言论可能占优势\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The words of the powerful may prevail in other spheres of human experience
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.31,0:17:57.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.15,0:18:01.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但对科学来说 最关键的是证据\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but in science, the only thing that counts is the evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.15,0:18:03.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以及争议本身的逻辑性\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the logic of the argument itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.65,0:18:07.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}佩恩解释了安妮坎农的恒星光谱序列\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cecilia Payne's interpretation of Annie Jump Cannon's sequence
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.06,0:18:12.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}使我们可以理解恒星生命的故事\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of stellar spectra made it possible for us to read the life stories of the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.06,0:18:19.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并且根据这个从它燃烧的终点追溯回它的起源\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and to trace the story of life itself back to its beginnings in their fiery deaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.44,0:18:31.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有很多种恒星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are many kinds of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.25,0:18:33.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一些像太阳般明亮\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some are bright like the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.82,0:18:35.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有些暗淡\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some are dim.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.95,0:18:40.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最大的恒星比最小的要大上千万倍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The greatest stars are ten million\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}times larger than the smallest ones
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.32,0:18:42.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有些恒星古老的超出想象\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some stars are old beyond imagining,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.93,0:18:46.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}超过100亿岁\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}more than ten billion years of age.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.13,0:18:48.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有些才刚刚诞生\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Others are being born right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.20,0:18:55.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当原子在恒星的核心中融合\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When atoms fuse in the hearts of stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.20,0:18:56.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们发出星光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they make starlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.51,0:18:58.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恒星从杂物中诞生\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Stars are born in litters,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.44,0:19:02.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由星际云的气体和灰尘组成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}formed from the gas and dust of interstellar clouds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.11,0:19:05.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不同恒星的质量差异\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The mass of the individual stars in a litter
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.05,0:19:09.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从小的那些 并不比最大的行星大多少\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can range from the runts--not much larger than the largest planets--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.45,0:19:12.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}到大的那些超巨星 让太阳都相形见绌\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the supergiant stars that dwarf the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.39,0:19:22.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}猎户座腰带下方星云中的恒星刚刚诞生\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The stars in the nebula below Orion's Belt are newborns,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.33,0:19:24.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}差不多500万岁\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}around five million years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.07,0:19:29.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还被包裹在诞生时的气体和灰尘中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and still swaddled in the gas and dust that gave birth to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.51,0:19:32.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}昂宿星团中的恒星已经到了蹒跚学步的年纪\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The stars in the Pleiades are already toddlers,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.68,0:19:34.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1亿岁左右\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about 100 million years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.58,0:19:36.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们已经甩开了气体和灰尘的遮盖\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They've shed their blankets of gas and dust,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.71,0:19:40.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但依然被彼此的引力束缚在一起\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but they're still bound together by their mutual gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.58,0:19:42.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}再过几亿年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Another few hundred million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.52,0:19:45.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们才会各奔东西\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they'll drift apart and go their separate ways,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.15,0:19:47.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从此再不相见\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}never to meet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.69,0:19:51.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}北斗星中的大部分恒星已经是青少年了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most of the stars of the Big Dipper are adolescents,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.33,0:19:53.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}5亿岁左右\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}roughly half a billion years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.90,0:19:56.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们已经离开了出生时的星团\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They've already drifted apart from their birth cluster,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.50,0:19:59.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不过 我们还是能找到它们共同的祖先\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}although we can still trace their common ancestry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.57,0:20:02.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最终 它们会散落在银河系中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Eventually, they'll spread out around the Milky Way galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.01,0:20:05.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是大部分常见的星座\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But most of the familiar constellations
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.88,0:20:09.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是由完全不相关的恒星混合而成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are a mix of entirely unrelated stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.25,0:20:11.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有些暗淡而相距不远\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}some faint and nearby,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.05,0:20:14.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有些明亮远远相隔\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}others bright and far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.72,0:20:18.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的太阳呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our own Sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.29,0:20:23.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从几光年开外看去 也很难找到其它相近的恒星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From the distance of even a few light-years, it's hard to find amidst the other stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.73,0:20:25.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那个\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.36,0:20:28.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的太阳已进中年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our Sun is middle-aged
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.90,0:20:30.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}离开出生地也很远了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a long way from where it was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.87,0:20:34.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从同一个星际云诞生的姐妹星们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its sister stars hatched from the same interstellar cloud,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.37,0:20:37.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}分散在银河系各处\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are dispersed throughout the galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.24,0:20:39.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}许多都有它们各自的行星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Many of them have their own planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.91,0:20:41.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}或许有些已经孕育了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Perhaps some of them nurture
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.81,0:20:44.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}智慧生物和生命的进化\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the evolution of life and intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.91,0:20:47.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}夜空中的大多数恒星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most of the stars in our night sky
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.05,0:20:50.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}会环绕一个或多个恒星小伙伴运行\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}actually orbit around one or more stellar companions.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.72,0:20:53.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在这种双星或者多星的系统内 靠我们的肉眼\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With the naked eye, we usually can't see the fainter members
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.82,0:20:56.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}通常看不到较暗的那些星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in such double and multiple star systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.79,0:21:00.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在有3个太阳的世界里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On a world with three suns,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.73,0:21:02.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很少有夜晚\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the nights would be rare
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.67,0:21:06.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}白天也在红色和蓝色中交替\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the days might alternate between red and blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.81,0:21:15.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恒星的坍缩是注定的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is the destiny of stars to collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.58,0:21:19.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}抬头看向夜空 所看到的成千上万的星星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Of the thousands of stars you see when you look up at the night sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.75,0:21:23.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每一个都活在两次坍缩之间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every one of them is living in an interval between two collapses...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.25,0:21:26.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}黑暗的星际气体云团的第一次坍缩\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an initial collapse of a dark, interstellar gas cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.12,0:21:27.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}形成了恒星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to form the star,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.76,0:21:30.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}明亮恒星的最后一次坍缩\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a final collapse of the luminous star
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.33,0:21:33.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是它的生命尽头\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on its way to its ultimate fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.10,0:21:37.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有外力干扰的情况下 引力使恒星收缩\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gravity makes stars contract, unless some other force intervenes
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.03,0:21:40.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳是个炽热气体组成的大球体\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun is a great, big ball of incandescent gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.37,0:21:43.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}核心的超高温气体\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The super hot gas in its core
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.34,0:21:45.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}促使太阳向外扩张\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}pushes the Sun to expand outward.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.37,0:21:48.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与此同时 太阳的引力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the same time,the Sun's own gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.21,0:21:50.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}又使它向内收缩\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}pulls it inward to contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.28,0:21:54.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的太阳处在两种力稳定平衡的状态\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And our Sun is poised between these two forces in a stable equilibrium
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.88,0:21:58.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}引力和核爆炸\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}between gravity and nuclear fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.05,0:21:59.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这种平衡会继续\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a balance it will maintain
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.56,0:22:01.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}保持40亿年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for another four billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.89,0:22:04.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳消耗氢气\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But as the Sun consumes hydrogen,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.23,0:22:07.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的核心慢慢的收缩\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its core very slowly shrinks,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.20,0:22:10.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而它的表面却在逐步的扩张\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the Sun's surface gradually expands in response.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.70,0:22:15.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在几百万年的时间里 过程很缓慢 不易察觉\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It happens very slowly,imperceptibly, over the course of millions of years
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.40,0:22:17.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但对于10亿年来说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in about a billion years,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.51,0:22:21.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳会比现在亮出百分之10\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Sun will be ten percent brighter than it is today
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.31,0:22:26.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}百分之10 听上去不多\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ten percent may not sound like much,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.32,0:22:30.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但这些额外的热量会对地球造成很大的影响\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but that extra heat will have a big effect on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.43,0:22:40.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当太阳最终耗尽它的核燃料\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When the Sun finally exhausts its nuclear fuel
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.10,0:22:42.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}40或者50亿年后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}four or five billion years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.77,0:22:46.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}气体会冷却 压力会下降\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its gas will cool and the pressure will fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.40,0:22:51.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳的内部无法继续支撑外层的重量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun's interior can no longer support the weight of the outer layers
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.04,0:22:54.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最初的坍缩再次继续\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the initial collapse will resume.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.41,0:22:56.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}万物都没有永恒\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nothing lasts forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.28,0:22:58.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恒星也会死\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even the stars die.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.78,0:23:03.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}氦 100亿年来氢聚变的灰烬\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Helium, the ash of ten billion years of hydrogen fusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.05,0:23:05.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在核心中汇聚\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has built up in the core.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.29,0:23:07.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有核爆炸支持它的重量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With no nuclear fire to sustain its weight,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.86,0:23:13.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}内核坍缩 温度高的开始将氦聚合成碳和氧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the core collapses until it becomes hot enough to start fusing helium into carbon and oxygen
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.73,0:23:17.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳内核的温度比以前高很多\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The core of the Sun is now much hotter than it was before.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.60,0:23:20.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的大气急剧膨胀\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its atmosphere rapidly expands.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.37,0:23:23.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在接下来的10亿年里 它膨胀到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Over the next billion years, it'll become bloated
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.47,0:23:25.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}超过现在体积的100倍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to more than 100 times its original size
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.98,0:23:29.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}变成一颗红巨星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a red giant star.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.08,0:23:34.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它将会覆盖并吞噬\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It will envelop and devour
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.32,0:23:36.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}水星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the planets Mercury...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.42,0:23:41.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}金星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}...and Venus...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.16,0:23:48.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很可能还有地球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}...and possibly the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.27,0:23:52.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我认为\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I like to think that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.13,0:23:54.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在那之前的几千万年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}tens of millions of years before that far distant future,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.67,0:23:57.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果地球上还有生命诞生\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if there still be life born of Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.91,0:24:01.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们应该已经在其它星球找到了新家\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it will have found new homes among the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.48,0:24:05.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一旦太阳燃尽所有的氦\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once the Sun burns through its helium,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.58,0:24:07.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它就开始变得非常不稳定\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it will become highly unstable,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.78,0:24:10.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将它的外围甩向太空\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}casting off its outer layers into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.09,0:24:14.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}超级炙热的裸露核心\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The exposed, super hot core
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.86,0:24:18.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}发出高能量的紫外线 潮水般淹没四周\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will flood its surroundings with high-energy ultraviolet light.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.20,0:24:25.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}原子们发着光 疯狂的剧烈活动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The atoms will perform a wild, fluorescent dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.21,0:24:34.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳会像蛋奶酥一样的收缩塌陷\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun will collapse like a souffle
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.14,0:24:37.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}缩小到地球体积的几百倍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}shrinking a hundredfold to the size of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.31,0:24:42.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}到那时 太阳极度紧密 过度拥挤的电子开始相互排挤\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And at that point, the Sun will be so dense that its overcrowded electrons will push back,
