Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.35,0:30:41.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}星座\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Constellations.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.63,0:30:48.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是澳洲土著\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the Aboriginal people of Australia
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.00,0:30:51.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}注意到了黑影的形状\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}saw a pattern in the darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.16,0:30:53.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}贯穿银河\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}running through the Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.27,0:30:58.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看上去像鸸鹋 一种大鸟 一种澳洲大陆本土动物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They saw an emu, a large bird native to this continent.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.30,0:31:02.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它并不是由星星组成 而是在没有星星的地方悄然出现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Not in the stars,but in the absence of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.38,0:31:08.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有不用的方式来看星空\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are so many ways to look at the night sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.15,0:31:11.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}上百万年的时间里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For a million years or more, we've watched the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.18,0:31:12.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}发生了很多事\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And a lot's happened in that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.89,0:31:16.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的银河系中超新星爆炸大约100年一次\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Supernova explode in our galaxy about once a century.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.79,0:31:21.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果我们把所有遥望星空的夜晚压缩成一分钟\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If we could compress all those nights of stargazing into a single minute
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.66,0:31:24.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是我们可以看到的景象\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this is what we would see.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.24,0:31:31.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果把我们的眼睛比做望远镜\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, if our eyes were telescopes,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.40,0:31:34.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}口径和车轮一样大\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if they were light buckets as big as wagon wheels
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.14,0:31:37.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们又可以识别不仅仅一种光时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and our vision was not limited to just one kind of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.81,0:31:42.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们看到的银河系就是这样的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then this is the Milky Way we would see.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.25,0:31:44.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}近红外光中的星系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A galaxy in near-infrared light
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.98,0:31:47.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}触手般四处蔓延的尘埃\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with streaming tendrils of dust
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.15,0:31:49.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}被爆炸的超新星猛烈地甩出\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hurled outward by those exploding supernovas,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.86,0:31:54.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在无数星星的映衬下显现出来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}silhouetted against a backdrop of countless stars
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.69,0:31:57.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大约7500光年以外\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}About 7,500 light-years away,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.66,0:31:59.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}银河系的另一端\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in another part of our galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.90,0:32:02.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有一场巨变\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there is a place of upheaval
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.07,0:32:04.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}规模大得难以想象\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on an inconceivable scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.68,0:32:15.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是船底座星云\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is the Carina Nebula.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.85,0:32:18.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一台恒星制造机\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A star-making machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.06,0:32:26.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}光线要用50年的时间才能贯穿\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It takes a ray of light 50 years to cross it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.07,0:32:32.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}巨大的恒星在这里诞生\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The titanic stars born here
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.44,0:32:37.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}强烈的紫外线辐射烤焦了周围的气体和尘埃\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sear the surrounding gas and dust with their fierce ultraviolet radiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.74,0:32:40.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}巨大的恒星死亡时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When a massive star dies,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.21,0:32:43.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将它自己炸成碎片\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it blows itself to smithereens.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.12,0:32:48.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的物质被推得四处纷飞\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its substance is propelled across the vastness
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.85,0:32:50.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}被星光搅动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to be stirred by starlight
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.89,0:32:53.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}被引力汇聚\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and gathered up by gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.19,0:32:55.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由恒星变成尘埃\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Stars to dust
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.06,0:32:57.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}再由尘埃变为恒星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and dust to stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.90,0:33:00.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙中 没有废物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the cosmos, nothing is wasted.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.90,0:33:06.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但是恒星的质量有一个上限\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But there's an upper limit to how massive a star can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.14,0:33:11.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}17世纪时 爱德蒙・哈雷\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Back in the 17th century, when Edmond Halley
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.58,0:33:14.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}跨过赤道 绘制南方的星座图\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}crossed the equator to map the southern constellations,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.28,0:33:17.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}海山二看上去只是一颗暗星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Eta Carinae seemed like just another faint star.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.28,0:33:17.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}一个位于船底星座
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.55,0:33:20.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但到了1843年 海山二\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in 1843, Eta Carinae
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.38,0:33:23.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}突然变成了天空中第二亮的星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}suddenly became the second brightest star in the sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.12,0:33:25.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只是比天狼星稍暗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}outshined only by Sirius.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.82,0:33:28.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从此开始爆发\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it's been flipping out ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.46,0:33:33.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那个哑铃形的云团\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That dumbbell-shaped cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.67,0:33:36.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就是爆发的膨胀残余\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the expanding remnant of that event.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.41,0:33:44.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}中心是一颗疯狂的恒星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At its center is one crazy star.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.51,0:33:46.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}说到不稳定\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Talk about unstable
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.41,0:33:49.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}海山二比太阳的质量大出至少100倍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Eta Carinae is at least 100 times more massive than the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.02,0:33:53.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并且发出比太阳多500万倍的光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and pouring out five million times more light.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.32,0:33:58.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它一直在挑战恒星质量的上限\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's pushing the upper limit of what a star can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.83,0:34:01.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有 有证据显示 海山二\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What's more, there's evidence that Eta Carinae
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.66,0:34:05.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}饱受它那邪恶兄弟的重力折磨\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is being gravitationally tormented by an evil twin--
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.43,0:34:08.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是一颗绕它运行的恒星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}another massive star in orbit around it
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.50,0:34:12.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}之间的距离就像土星到太阳的距离\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as close as Saturn is to the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.41,0:34:16.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}超级巨大的恒星内核发出大量的光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The core of a supermassive star pours out so much light
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.38,0:34:19.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以致向外的压力盖过了恒星的引力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the outward pressure can overwhelm the star's gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.91,0:34:22.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果恒星过于巨大\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If a star is too massive,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.38,0:34:25.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的辐射压力超过它的引力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its radiation pressure overpowers its gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.05,0:34:27.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就会将这颗星炸裂\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and blows the star apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.69,0:34:31.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}海山二的命运\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The fate of Eta Carinae was sealed
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.69,0:34:34.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在几百万年前诞生时就已经注定\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when it was born millions of years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.13,0:34:36.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当它最终爆炸时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When it finally does blow up
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.23,0:34:38.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}说不定 已经爆炸了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and who knows, maybe it already has;
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.57,0:34:41.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}毕竟 我们看到的光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}after all, we're looking at it by light that left the star
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.30,0:34:43.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是7500年前发出的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}7,500 years ago--
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.80,0:34:47.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那会是我们从没见过的大灾难\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it will be a cataclysm unlike anything we've seen before.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.77,0:34:49.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}极超新星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A hypernova.
