Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.02,0:35:36.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}现在 你可能好奇\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Right about now, you're probably asking yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.69,0:35:39.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们安全吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"Are we safe?"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.13,0:35:41.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果海山二爆炸\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If Eta Carinae blows up,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.49,0:35:44.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球怎么办\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what happens to Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.16,0:35:47.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}放心吧 地球不会有事\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Rest assured, Earth will be just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.37,0:35:51.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}记住 我们离它7500光年呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Remember, we're 7,500 light-years away from Eta Carinae.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.47,0:35:53.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恒星放出的辐射强度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The intensity of radiation from a star,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.61,0:35:55.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}即使是一颗爆炸的恒星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even an exploding star,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.48,0:35:57.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}随着距离急剧下降\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}falls off rapidly with distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.71,0:36:01.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}即使这样 海山二的谢幕演出\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But still, Eta Carinae in its death throes
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.15,0:36:03.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}依然会非常精彩\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will put on quite a show.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.15,0:36:05.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它会点亮南半球的夜空\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It will light up the night of the southern hemisphere
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.65,0:36:07.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}亮得如同月亮一样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with the brightness of a second moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.02,0:36:12.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}奉献上最激动人心的告别演出\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The most dramatic swan song a star can sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.63,0:36:20.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的祖先崇拜太阳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our ancestors worshipped the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.33,0:36:23.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们绝不是愚蠢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And they were far from foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.40,0:36:27.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对太阳和恒星的崇拜很有道理\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It makes good sense to revere the Sun and stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.14,0:36:29.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为我们是它们的孩子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because we are their children.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.54,0:36:32.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}岩石中的硅 空气中的氧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The silicon in the rocks, the oxygen in the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.01,0:36:36.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}DNA中的碳 摩天大楼中的铁\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the carbon in our DNA, the iron in our skyscrapers,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.88,0:36:39.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}珠宝中的银\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the silver in our jewelry
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.19,0:36:42.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都是恒星们几十亿年前创造的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were all made in stars billions of years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.02,0:36:46.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的星球 我们的社会 还有我们自己\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our planet, our society and we ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.73,0:36:49.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都是星尘\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are stardust.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.76,0:36:53.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是什么使原子们这么活跃\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, what is it that makes the atoms dance?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.93,0:36:56.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恒星的能量是如何转变为\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How is the energy of a star transformed
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.70,0:36:59.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}世界上所发生的一切呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into everything that happens in the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.74,0:37:01.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}什么是能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What is energy?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.01,0:37:03.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们都身处其中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're awash in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.71,0:37:06.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当氢原子在太阳中聚合\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When hydrogen atoms fuse inside the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.51,0:37:08.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}产生氦原子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they make helium atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.22,0:37:10.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这种核聚变发出一股能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And this fusion emits a burst of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.72,0:37:13.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可以在太阳内部游荡1千万年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that can wander inside the Sun for ten million years
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.02,0:37:16.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然后到达表面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before making its way to the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.52,0:37:19.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然后获得自由\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And once there, it's free to fly
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.06,0:37:21.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}直接向地球飞来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}straight from the Sun to the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.26,0:37:23.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就是可见光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as visible light.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.93,0:37:27.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果它撞击在叶子的表面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If it should strike the surface of a leaf,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.10,0:37:30.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它就被作为化学能量保存在了地球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it will be stored in the plant as chemical energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.07,0:37:32.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}日光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sunshine...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.11,0:37:33.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}变成月光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into moonshine.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.11,0:37:33.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fn方正黑体简体\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}这里指的是一种威士忌
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.39,0:37:57.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我能感受到我的大脑把葡萄酒的化学能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I can feel my brain turning the chemical energy of the wine
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.13,0:37:59.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}转变为思想的电能\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into the electrical energy of my thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.30,0:38:01.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}指挥我的声带\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and directing my vocal chords
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.07,0:38:03.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}产生我说话的声能\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to produce the acoustic energy of my voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.84,0:38:06.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这种能量的转换\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Such transformations of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.31,0:38:08.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}无时无刻都在发生\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are happening everywhere all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.91,0:38:10.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳的能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Energy from our star
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.58,0:38:12.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}驱动风和浪\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}drives the wind and the waves
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.61,0:38:14.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有我们四周的生命\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the life around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.45,0:38:17.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有这样大量的清洁能源是多么幸运的事情\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How lucky we are to have this vast source of clean energy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.92,0:38:21.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这简直是给所有人的天赐之物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}falling like manna from heaven on all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.86,0:38:23.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}敬 安妮・坎农\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To Annie Jump Cannon,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.79,0:38:25.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}亨丽爱塔・勒维特\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Henrietta Swan Leavitt
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.46,0:38:27.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有塞西莉亚・佩恩\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and Cecilia Payne
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.13,0:38:30.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}感谢她们开创了现代天文物理学\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for blazing the trail to modern astrophysics.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.10,0:38:34.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还要敬 太阳的所有姐妹们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And to all the sisters of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.94,0:38:43.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙中一切都逃不过改变\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's no refuge from change in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.94,0:38:46.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从现在以后的壹千万或两千万年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some ten or 20 million years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.81,0:38:49.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在宇宙中只是片刻\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it'll seem for a cosmic moment
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.12,0:38:52.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}彷佛猎户俄里翁终于要抓到七姐妹了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as if Orion is finally about to catch the seven sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.85,0:38:55.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但在他抓住她们之前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But before he has them in his clutches,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.46,0:38:59.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}猎户座最大的几颗恒星就会变成超新星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the biggest stars of Orion will go supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.16,0:39:02.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}猎户座对昂宿星座的追赶会从此停止\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Orion's pursuit of the Pleiades will finally end,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.30,0:39:03.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那七位姐妹\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the seven sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.80,0:39:09.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}会缓缓地投入银河系的臂弯\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will glide serenely into the waiting arms of the Milky Way
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.71,0:39:17.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们在地球上对太阳升起发出赞叹\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We on Earth marvel and rightly so-- at the return of our solitary Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.34,0:39:21.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在遥远的球状星云中 从一个环绕恒星的行星上看\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But from a planet orbiting a star in a distant globular cluster,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.72,0:39:24.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还能看到更多惊艳的黎明\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a still more glorious dawn awaits.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.09,0:39:28.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不是太阳升起\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Not a sunrise...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.26,0:39:31.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而是星系的升起\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but a galaxy rise.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.22,0:39:35.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}2千亿颗太阳照耀的早晨\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A morning filled with 200 billion suns.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.33,0:39:38.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}银河系的升起\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The rising of the Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.33,0:39:42.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}巨大的螺旋状伴随者坍塌的气体云团\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An enormous spiral form with collapsing gas clouds,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.07,0:39:45.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}凝结的行星系统 发光的超巨星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}condensing planetary systems, luminous supergiants,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.74,0:39:49.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}稳定的中年太阳，红巨星，白矮星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}stable middle-aged suns, red giants, white dwarfs,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.68,0:39:52.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}行星状星云 超新星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}planetary nebulas, supernovas,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.11,0:39:55.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}中子星 脉冲星 黑洞\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}neutron stars, pulsars, black holes
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.08,0:39:57.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有充分的理由认为\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and, there is every reason to think,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.62,0:40:01.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有其它的天体 我们尚未发现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}other exotic objects that we have yet to discover.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.92,0:40:05.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从这样的一个世界 高悬于银河系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From such a world, high above the Milky Way,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.79,0:40:10.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这么的清晰 清晰地如同我们世界起源时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would be clear, as it is beginning to be clear on our world,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.70,0:40:15.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们由原子和众星组成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we are made by the atoms and the stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.04,0:40:17.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的物质 我们的形态\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that our matter and our form
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.10,0:40:21.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由伟大而古老的宇宙锻造\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are forged by the great and ancient cosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.74,0:40:24.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们也是这个宇宙的一部分\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of which we are a part.
